title: Prabowo's 'Red and White' cabinet is Indonesia's largest since 1960s
description: Indonesia's new President Prabowo Subianto has officially sworn in his cabinet -- the country's largest since the 1960s. Consisting of 109 ministers, vice ministers and heads of government agencies, Mr Prabowo has named it his "Red and White" cabinet -- in reference to the colours of the national flag. Also on the slate are politicians from a coalition of seven parties, who had backed Mr Prabowo's victory in elections in February. Randy Mulyanto reports from Jakarta.
